<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:medium;">because its a pipe dream</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Where :</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Meet at Akannon Book in Plane of Knowledge.  <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>When :</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Sunday August 3rd , 2pm EST<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Why :</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Fun Social Adventure<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Who :</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> All Classes and Races, level 45+ preferred.  <br>
<!--EZCODE LIST START--><ul><li><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">If you are under level 45</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> and die more than 3 times, you will be offered a TL after 3rd rez that you better take (cus no more rezzes for you.)</li></ul><!--EZCODE LIST END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>How Long :</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A few hours until everyone mutiny's complaining of sore feet and lack of beer.<br>
<br>
Similar to another idea posted in the General forums...<br>
<br>
I would be up for a march around the world that would include not just Antonica, but Kunark, and would involve us moving at walking speed, but killing everything in our path.  Everyone traveling would be in raid format.  (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>extreme minimum level of 20</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->).<br>
<br>
This would be awesome fun.<br>
<br>
With at least one clicky cleric, we would be able to &quot;battle rez&quot; those who fall in the march so as not to leave anyone behind, but hopefully not too many would fall in battle if we do it right.<br>
<br>
Ideally, we would have several main tanks with assigned healers and slowers for them and their targets.  We wouldn't necessarily need crowd control except for when we pass cities or more populated areas.<br>
<br>
we should move with occasional AE radiating from the throng by way of bard songs or other to be sure we do not let any creatures that pass us go unscathed.<br>
<br>
Faction wise, if you see we are battlling something of which you do not want to take a faction hit, just do not partake in the encounter or we may march past some things without conflict.<br>
<br>
I personally, can afford to kill most anything so long as we do not linger and kill too many.<br>
<br>
Cities like Freeport and the like would be fun to slaughter as well.  I know paladins hate Freeport, (for good reason).  <br>
<br>
We will close ranks if we have to pass through cities so we don't have to kill so many that people will be concerned about faction. <br>
<br>
Anyway...<br>
<br>
See you there.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
